<!--
  Every user-facing string in the sources slice (PRD §6.10: English-first, string infrastructure
  from day one), in PRD §8.6 voice: from the couch, active, no jargon — "Add from your phone", never
  "LAN pairing session".

  Two things are deliberately still in Kotlin, and both are view-model API shape rather than
  oversight: the `validation` and `status` channels are `StateFlow<String?>`, so resourcing them
  means changing what a view model publishes, which is a design change and not a string sweep.
-->
